olive oil
1 tin Pineapple Slices
1 packet Diced Chicken
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
½ lemon
1 cucumber
1 bag Slaw Mix
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Smokey Aioli
1 bag coriander
1 sachet Mild Caribbean Jerk Seasoning

• Drain and chop pineapple
• In a bowl, combine diced chicken,
seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil
• Heat a frying pan over high heat with
a drizzle of olive oil. Cook chicken
and pineapple, tossing occasionally,
until browned and cooked through,
5-6 mins
• Add sweet chilli sauce and toss to
coat, 1 min

• Meanwhile, roughly chop cucumber.
Slice lemon into wedges
• In a second bowl, combine slaw,
cucumber, a squeeze of lemon juice
and a drizzle of oil. Season to taste

• Microwave tortillas on a plate in
10 second bursts, until warm
• Spread smokey aioli over tortillas
• Fill tortillas with slaw, chicken and
pineapple
• Tear over coriander and serve with
remaining lemon wedges